# Demo Scenario

### Step 1 — User Logs In
- A student opens the system.
- They authenticate using email or school ID.

### Step 2 — User Creates a Record
- User creates a new record (organization, opportunity, or event).
- System saves the record to the database.

### Step 3 — Another User Interacts With That Record
- A second user views the newly created record.
- They take an action (save it, follow it, register, etc.).
- The system updates the database accordingly.

### Step 4 — System Displays Updated Results
- Both users can now see the updated state.
- The system confirms actions, showing real-time updates.

This scenario demonstrates the core user workflow and the value of the system.

